  <description type="morphology">Stems sparsely to moderately hispido-strigose and stipitate-glandular. Distal cauline leaf blades ovate to lanceolate, (12–)16–39(–55) × 5–15 mm, margins with few long-hispido-strigose cilia, faces sparsely to moderately hispido-strigose and stipitate-glandular. Subtending bracts ovate, usually large (7–22 × 2–6 mm), leaflike, well differentiated. Involucres 6.7–10.3 mm. Phyllaries lanceolate to triangular-lanceolate, moderately strigose and stipitate-glandular. Ray laminae (8–)9.8–14.5 mm. Cypsela faces sparsely to moderately strigose. 2n = 18, 36.</description>
